            <biogHist>
                <p>Angus Gunn was born to parents Donald Gunn, a crofter and Ann Gunn n√©e
                    Macfarlane. He married Christina Mackenzie and in 1841 the census records them
                    living in the village of North Dell in the parish of Barvas, Cross quoad sacra
                    with their two children: John and Ann. At this time, Angus is recorded as being
                    a 'tenant'; later censuses record him as being a crofter. In the censuses for
                    1851 and 1861, a grandson Donald Murray, son of Ann who was unmarried, is in the
                    household; by 1871, Angus is a widower and is recorded living with daughter Ann
                    (who appears to have married and is now a MacDonald, but is also widowed by this
                    time), grandson Murdo MacDonald (19) and grand-daughter Christina MacDonald
                    (13). </p>
                <p>Angus died in August 1875 in North Dell, Barvas due to an unknown cause, having
                    been ill for the week prior to his death; his illegitimate grandson Donald
                    Murray is recorded as the informant.</p>
